    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-06T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="450"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d450">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">660P.116/29b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cole</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-06T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 6, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. Department’s No. 55, December 5, 1934, 5 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d450fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1934v02#pg_616">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid</hi>., p. 616</ref>.</note> Please expedite
                    submission of desired report which should show definitely whether American trade
                    is now receiving most-favored-nation treatment in Latvia and, if not, precisely
                    wherein such treatment is being denied. Department is requesting by cable
                    similar report from Legation at Kaunas to which you should forward copy of
                    Tallinn report No. 43<note n="3" xml:id="d450fn3">October 6, 1934, <ref
                            target="frus1934v02#pg_130">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>, p. 130</ref>.</note> to serve as model.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
